    <briefdescription>
<para>Three-position switch (ON-OFF-ON / spring-centred) on two pins. Emits 0 / 1 / 2 over CAN (MULTIPOS dispatch). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A MULTIPOS-family input (N = 3) — self-registers via <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1MultiPosInput" kindref="compound">MultiPosInput</ref>, which owns the debounce / emit-on-change / forceReport contract. This class supplies only the read.</para>
<para>Two pins, one per outer throw; the centre needs no pin of its own:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>pin A active → position 0</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>pin B active → position 2</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>neither → position 1 (centre — a real, emitted position)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Mirrors <ref refid="namespaceDcsBios" kindref="compound">DcsBios</ref> <computeroutput><ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1Switch3Pos" kindref="compound">Switch3Pos</ref></computeroutput>: if both pins read active (impossible mechanically — a bounce during a throw), pin A wins (position 0); the debounce absorbs the transient either way. Because the centre is resolved directly, <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1Switch3Pos_1ab21780e7a61a1d79d6238b5d17d3b5ec" kindref="member">readRaw()</ref> never returns NO_POSITION — the base&apos;s hold-last path is unused.</para>
<para>One-hot read (reverse = false, default): the active pin reads LOW (closed to GND). reverse = true inverts it (active pin reads HIGH). <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1Switch3Pos_1a841872d6f33cf299101cfe37e7c18310" kindref="member">configure()</ref> does not enable internal pull-ups; the schematic supplies input bias (typically 10 kΩ to +3.3V, switch to GND).</para>
<para>Used by: AN/ASN-41 LAT/LON slew (spring-centred momentary L / centre / R). </para>
    </detaileddescription>
